Lidocaine had no significant (P > 0.05) effect on these values when applied to normokalaemic hearts (Fig. 7C). Thus, A and τ took values of 81.1 ± 3.05 ms and 56.92 ± 10.29 ms in the epicardium and 104.47 ± 13.69 ms and 97.17 ± 36.22 ms in the endocardium, with \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
